solution.p:
By Definition , the work done in moving the object from x = 1 meters
to x = 16 meters by the force F(x) is


W = \int_1^{16} F(x)\dee{x}
= \int_1^{16} \frac{a}{\sqrt{x}}\dee{x}
= \Big[2a\sqrt{x}\,\Big]_{x=1}^{x=16}
=6a


To have W=18, we need a=3.

